14:
I can't find it anywhere! I'm looking
for a book that details the secret art
of body transfiguration!
18:
Body transfiguration? Like, for
yourself? I thought you said you
were proud of who you were?
21:
Of course I am! But that doesn't
mean there aren't some parts about
me that I'd like to change—I'm free
to do so, after all!
24:
*sigh* To be honest, I just think the
students would take me more
seriously if I were a little taller...
31:
Yes! Speaking of which, you lot
wouldn't happen to know anyone
familiar with this sort of magic,
would you? That includes those on
the outside!
34:
I'm not sure... It's not every day you
come across that type of magic.
Or... wait, maybe I do know
someone...
50:
This is amazing! How can you live in
such a state?
53:
Ohoho! That's simple, my
dear—practice! And as you can no
doubt tell by my appearance, I've
had plenty of time to do just that!
56:
Indeed! With access to YOUR
techniques, I won't ever look like a
child again!
60:
Oh, what am I thinking?! This sort of
magic is DEFINITELY forbidden! I'll be
chased out of the academy even if I
tried!
63:
I just want to have longer legs,
maybe slim up my waist, fix my
nose... AND clean up my skin! Is that
too much to ask?
67:
It certainly isn't too little to ask... I'm
afraid the exact modifications you
desire complicate matters.
69:
Reincarnation is out of the question,
as is fabricating an entirely new
body... But perhaps there is another
way!
77:
A m-mushroom? What exactly are
you getting at?!
81:
Why, nothing at all... They're just
regular nutrient-packed
mushrooms! The sort little lasses like
you would do well to eat!
84:
I'm somewhat of an expert on
bones. Trust me—if you want them
to grow, nutrition is your best bet!
88:
I'll have you know that I stopped
growing a long time ago!
92:
Hmph, I guess I'll hold off on that
transfiguration business then. My
time would be much better spent
conversing with you instead!
94:
I can't let superficial motivations
guide me! The knowledge I could
glean from someone as seasoned
and wise as you is MUCH more
valuable!
97:
Well, I don't know about all THAT!
Calling me wise might be a stretch...
101:
Tonight, I'll be the student for a
change! Tor Leleni, ready for class!
110:
Good morning—wait, what?! Is it
morning already?!
116:
Huh? You mean you've been up this
whole time?!
120:
Well, yes, I just couldn't help myself!
All this magic talk was so
enlightening! I couldn't let a single
minute go to waste!
124:
Ohoho, indeed! It seems our little
professor here is just as good a
student as she is a teacher!
126:
It's been ages since these old bones
have felt so invigorated!
131:
Master Regitare is incredibly
knowledgeable on all sorts of
subjects—elemental gems, mana,
ether, you name it!
133:
But my favorite would have to be
the tale of how he first met the
sprites! I'm sure the students back
home would love to hear that one!
137:
Now that's a splendid idea! I'll gather
up everything I learned last night
and share it with my students! I'm
sure they'll get a kick out of it!
140: Just you wait, kids! I'm... I'm—
153:
Ah, that would be my bad, dear boy.
It always slips my noggin that you
fleshy creatures actually need to
sleep!
160:
*snore* Class is starting! To your...
seats...
165:
Even in her dreams, she's still
teaching.
168:
Ohoho! Those whippersnappers
don't know how lucky they are to
have such a wonderful teacher!
172: Hey! No running in the halls!
